<item>
            <title>[FLINK-13452] Pipelined region failover strategy does not recover Job if checkpoint cannot be read</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-13452</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The job does not recover if a checkpoint cannot be read and &lt;tt&gt;jobmanager.execution.failover-strategy&lt;/tt&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;&quot;region&quot;&lt;/em&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Analysis&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;RestartCallback&lt;/tt&gt; created by &lt;tt&gt;AdaptedRestartPipelinedRegionStrategyNG&lt;/tt&gt; throws a &lt;tt&gt;RuntimeException&lt;/tt&gt; if no checkpoints could be read. When the restart is invoked in a separate thread pool, the exception is swallowed. See:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/21621fbcde534969b748f21e9f8983e3f4e0fb1d/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/executiongraph/failover/AdaptedRestartPipelinedRegionStrategyNG.java#L117-L119&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/21621fbcde534969b748f21e9f8983e3f4e0fb1d/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/executiongraph/failover/AdaptedRestartPipelinedRegionStrategyNG.java#L117-L119&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/21621fbcde534969b748f21e9f8983e3f4e0fb1d/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/executiongraph/restart/FixedDelayRestartStrategy.java#L65&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/21621fbcde534969b748f21e9f8983e3f4e0fb1d/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/executiongraph/restart/FixedDelayRestartStrategy.java#L65&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected behavior&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Job should restart&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
